data.description: Welcome to the picturesque Edinburgh Community. The captivating entrance is breathtaking with a beautiful stone tower surrounded by beautifully manicured green spaces, fishing ponds, fountains, and a magnificent view of the breathtaking mountains. The Edinburgh Community is a lifestyle. The intimate, unique neighborhood features walking trails surrounded by forestry, a community pool, and the highly sought after, award winning John Adams Elementary School. In this captivating community, walking to and from school is a way of life. This stunning 4 bedroom 3.5 bath home is steps away from the entrance of John Adams. Nestled against beautiful mountain views, this home has a great deal of privacy in the rear! Upon entering the front door, you are greeted with soaring ceiling heights of a beautiful two story foyer which frames a beautiful staircase adorned with wrought iron spindles! Downstairs, you'll find a formal dining area with columns, and beautiful wood details. A large well appointed kitchen opens to an eat in breakfast area, and one of two family living spaces. A master bedroom with large bath is tucked away from the downstairs living space. Upstairs, you'll find a second family space with wood flooring, and a second master bedroom with an oversized, luxurious bath, and very large walk in closet. The upstairs level features three bedrooms and two full baths. After a long day, relax on the extended covered patio or front porch surrounded with beautiful, and thoughtfully selected landscaping. Perfect location! Convenient drive to Eastman, JCMC, and HVM. All information deemed correct, buyer/buyer's agent to verify.
